		    <title class="- topic/title ">
			      <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">12.301</ph> Solicitation provisions and contract clauses for the acquisition of commercial items.</title>
		    <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
			      <ol id="d699e13" class="- topic/ol ">
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d713e17" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            In accordance with <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                        format="html"
                        scope="external"
                        class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C. 3307</xref>, contracts for the acquisition of commercial items shall, to the maximum extent practicable, include only those clauses—</p>
					          <ol id="d699e26" class="- topic/ol ">
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d713e30" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                Required to implement provisions of law or executive orders applicable to the acquisition of commercial items; or</p>
						            </li>
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d713e39" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                Determined to be consistent with customary commercial practice.</p>
						            </li>
					          </ol>
				        </li>
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d713e50" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            Insert the following provisions in solicitations for the acquisition of commercial items, and clauses in solicitations and contracts for the acquisition of commercial items:</p>
					          <ol id="d699e56" class="- topic/ol ">
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d713e60" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                
								                <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">The provision at <xref href="FAR-i52_212-1.dita#i52_212-1"
                                 base="i1060447"
                                 outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                 class="- topic/xref ">52.212-1</xref>
								                </i>,<i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Instructions to Offerors-Commercial Items.</i>This provision provides a single, streamlined set of instructions to be used when soliciting offers for commercial items and is incorporated in the solicitation by reference (see Block 27 a, <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">SF 1449</xref>). The contracting officer may tailor these instructions or provide additional instructions tailored to the specific acquisition in accordance with <xref href="FAR-i1113286.dita#i1113286"
                              base="i1113286"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">12.302</xref>.</p>
						            </li>
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d713e84" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                
								                <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">The provision at</i>
								                <xref href="FAR-i1060550.dita#i1060550"
                              base="i1060550"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.212-3</xref>, <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Offeror Representations and Certifications-Commercial Items</i>. This provision provides a single, consolidated list of representations and certifications for the acquisition of commercial items and is attached to the solicitation for offerors to complete. This provision may not be tailored except in accordance with <xref href="FAR-i1126600.dita#i1126600"
                              base="i1126600"
                              outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                              class="- topic/xref ">subpart  1.4</xref>. Use the provision with its Alternate I in solicitations issued by DoD, NASA, or the Coast Guard.</p>
						            </li>
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d713e105" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                
								                <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">The clause at</i>
								                <xref href="FAR-i1060971.dita#i1060971"
                              base="i1060971"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.212-4</xref>, <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Contract Terms and Conditions-Commercial Items</i>. This clause includes terms and conditions which are, to the maximum extent practicable, consistent with customary commercial practices and is incorporated in the solicitation and contract by reference (see Block 27, <xref href="https://www.gsa.gov/forms-library/solicitationcontractorder-commercial-items"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">SF 1449</xref>). Use this clause with its Alternate I when a time-and-materials or labor-hour contract will be awarded. The contracting officer may tailor this clause in accordance with <xref href="FAR-i1113286.dita#i1113286"
                              base="i1113286"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">12.302</xref>.</p>
						            </li>
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d713e130" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(4)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                
								                <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">The clause at</i>
								                <xref href="FAR-i52_212_5.dita#i52_212_5"
                              base="i1061237"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.212-5</xref>, <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Contract Terms and Conditions Required to Implement Statutes or Executive Orders-Commercial Items</i>. This clause incorporates by reference only those clauses required to implement provisions of law or Executive orders applicable to the acquisition of commercial items.The contracting officer shall attach this clause to the solicitation and contract and, using the appropriate clause prescriptions, indicate which, if any, of the additional clauses cited in <xref href="FAR-i52_212_5.dita#i52_212_5"
                              base="i1061237"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.212-5</xref>(b) or (c) are applicable to the specific acquisition. Some of the clauses require fill-in; the fill-in language should be inserted as directed by <xref href="FAR-i1064663.dita#i1064663"
                              base="i1064663"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.104</xref>(d). When cost information is obtained pursuant to <xref href="FAR-i1109360.dita#i1109360"
                              base="i1109360"
                              outputclass="fm:Part"
                              class="- topic/xref ">part  15</xref> to establish the reasonableness of prices for commercial items, the contracting officer shall insert the clauses prescribed for this purpose in an addendum to the solicitation and contract. This clause may not be tailored.</p>
							              <ol id="d699e155" class="- topic/ol ">
								                <li class="- topic/li ">
									                  <p id="d713e159" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph>
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
										                    Use the clause with its Alternate I when the head of the agency has waived the examination of records by the Comptroller General in accordance with <xref href="FAR-i1091029.dita#i1091029"
                                    base="i1091029"
                                    outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">25.1001</xref>.</p>
								                </li>
								                <li props="Runin" class="- topic/li ">
									                  <p id="d713e171" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph>
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
										                    
									                  </p>
									                  <ol id="d699e177" class="- topic/ol ">
										                    <li class="- topic/li ">
											                      <p id="d713e181" class="- topic/p ">
                                    <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(A)</ph>
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
												                        If the acquisition will use funds appropriated or otherwise made available by the American Recovery and Reinvestment Act of 2009 (Pub. L. 111-5), the contracting officer shall use the clause with its Alternate II.</p>
										                    </li>
										                    <li props="Runin" class="- topic/li ">
											                      <p id="d713e190" class="- topic/p ">
                                    <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(B)</ph>
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
												                        
											                      </p>
											                      <ol id="d699e196" class="- topic/ol ">
												                        <li outputclass="italic" class="- topic/li ">
													                          <p id="d713e200" class="- topic/p ">
                                          <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                                          
                                          
                                          
                                          
                                          
                                          
                                          
                                          
                                          
                                          
                                          
														                            In the case of a bilateral contract modification that will use funds appropriated or otherwise made available by the American Recovery and Reinvestment Act of 2009, the contracting officer shall specify applicability of Alternate II to that modification.</p>
												                        </li>
												                        <li outputclass="italic" class="- topic/li ">
													                          <p id="d713e209" class="- topic/p ">
                                          <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                                          
                                          
                                          
                                          
                                          
                                          
                                          
                                          
                                          
                                          
                                          
														                            In the case of a task- or delivery-order contract in which not all orders will use funds appropriated or otherwise made available by the American Recovery and Reinvestment Act of 2009, the contracting officer shall specify the task or delivery orders to which Alternate II applies.</p>
												                        </li>
											                      </ol>
										                    </li>
										                    <li class="- topic/li ">
											                      <p id="d713e220" class="- topic/p ">
                                    <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(C)</ph>
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
                                    
												                        The contracting officer may not use Alternate I when Alternate II applies.</p>
										                    </li>
									                  </ol>
								                </li>
							              </ol>
						            </li>
					          </ol>
				        </li>
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d713e235" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            When the use of evaluation factors is appropriate, the contracting officer may—</p>
					          <ol id="d699e241" class="- topic/ol ">
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d713e245" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                Insert the provision at <xref href="FAR-i1060530.dita#i1060530"
                              base="i1060530"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.212-2</xref>, Evaluation-Commercial Items, in solicitations for commercial items (see <xref href="FAR-i1112620.dita#i1112620"
                              base="i1112620"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">12.602</xref>); or</p>
						            </li>
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d713e260" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                Include a similar provision containing all evaluation factors required by <xref href="FAR-i1112289.dita#i1112289"
                              base="i1112289"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">13.106</xref>, <xref href="FAR-i1110249.dita#i1110249"
                              base="i1110249"
                              outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                              class="- topic/xref ">subpart  14.2</xref> or <xref href="FAR-i1108536.dita#i1108536"
                              base="i1108536"
                              outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                              class="- topic/xref ">subpart  15.3</xref>, as an addendum (see <xref href="FAR-i1113286.dita#i1113286"
                              base="i1113286"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">12.302</xref>(d)).</p>
						            </li>
					          </ol>
				        </li>
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d713e283" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(d)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            Other required provisions and clauses. Notwithstanding prescriptions contained elsewhere in the FAR, when acquiring commercial items, contracting officers shall be required to use only those provisions and clauses prescribed in this part. The provisions and clauses prescribed in this part shall be revised, as necessary, to reflect the applicability of statutes and executive orders to the acquisition of commercial items.</p>
